<Layout title="Advertising Policy - Sojorn" description="How advertising works on Sojorn and what we refuse to do">
  <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-6 py-12">
    <h1 class="text-3xl font-bold mb-2 text-egyptianBlue">Advertising Policy</h1>
    <p class="mb-8 text-sm text-gray-500">Last Updated: February 21, 2026</p>

    <div class="prose prose-blue max-w-none text-gray-700">
      <p class="lead font-semibold">We run ads to fund the platform. Here is exactly how they work and everything we refuse to do.</p>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-bold mt-6 mb-4">1. Contextual Only, In-House Only</h2>
      <p class="mb-4">All advertising on Sojorn is served directly by MPLS LLC. We do not use third-party ad networks, demand-side platforms, or programmatic exchanges. No third-party scripts, tracking pixels, or advertising SDKs are embedded in sponsored content.</p>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-bold mt-6 mb-4">2. How Ad Relevance Works</h2>
      <p class="mb-4">Ad relevance is determined by a combination of contextual signals and your activity within Sojorn. We never track you across other apps or websites, and we never sell your data to third parties. The signals we use:</p>
      <ul class="list-disc pl-6 mb-4 space-y-1">
        <li><strong>Geography</strong> — advertisers select a neighborhood zone or radius, not an audience.</li>
        <li><strong>Content section</strong> — which part of the app the ad appears in (feed, quips, or beacons).</li>
        <li><strong>Interest categories</strong> — you explicitly choose categories you care about (food, events, services, real estate, etc.). You can change or clear your preferences at any time.</li>
        <li><strong>In-app engagement</strong> — your activity within Sojorn (likes, saves, and the types of content you interact with) helps us show ads that are relevant to your actual interests. This data stays within Sojorn and is never shared with advertisers or any third party.</li>
      </ul>
      <p class="mb-4">If you prefer not to have your in-app activity influence the ads you see, you can disable engagement-based ad relevance in your settings. You will still see ads, but they will be based only on geography, content section, and your declared interest categories.</p>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-bold mt-6 mb-4">3. Full Transparency</h2>
      <p class="mb-4">Sponsored content is always clearly labeled "Sponsored" or "Promoted" and is never disguised as organic content. Users can tap "Why am I seeing this?" on any sponsored post to see exactly which signals contributed to the placement — such as your neighborhood, the content section, your declared interests, and whether in-app engagement played a role.</p>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-bold mt-6 mb-4">4. Same Rules for Everyone</h2>
      <p class="mb-4">Sponsored content runs through the same AI moderation pipeline and community guidelines as all other content on Sojorn. There are no exceptions for paying advertisers. If sponsored content violates our guidelines, the ad is rejected and the advertiser is refunded.</p>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-bold mt-6 mb-4">5. Data Minimization for Advertisers</h2>
      <p class="mb-4">We provide advertisers with aggregate metrics only:</p>
      <ul class="list-disc pl-6 mb-4 space-y-1">
        <li>Neighborhood selected</li>
        <li>Total impressions (aggregate)</li>
        <li>Total taps (aggregate)</li>
        <li>Campaign duration</li>
      </ul>
      <p class="mb-4">That is it. We never share user-level data, demographics, device information, user IDs, or any other identifying information with advertisers.</p>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-bold mt-6 mb-4">6. Prohibited Ad Categories</h2>
      <p class="mb-4">The following categories of advertising are permanently banned from Sojorn:</p>
      <ul class="list-disc pl-6 mb-4 space-y-1">
        <li>Alcohol</li>
        <li>Gambling</li>
        <li>Political advertising of any kind</li>
        <li>Surveillance, tracking, or monitoring products</li>
        <li>Law enforcement agency promotions</li>
        <li>Data brokers or ad-tech companies</li>
        <li>Anything that contradicts our mission of user privacy and community safety</li>
      </ul>
      <p class="mb-4 text-sm text-gray-500">Note: This ban does not apply to public service announcements from municipal agencies promoting community events, public health resources, or civic programs. Those are welcome and may qualify for free community visibility under Section 7 below.</p>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-bold mt-6 mb-4">7. Community Services</h2>
      <p class="mb-4">Verified community service organizations — food shelves, shelters, crisis resources, volunteer organizations, and municipal public service programs — are eligible for free promoted visibility on Beacons. This is not advertising; it is part of Sojorn's mission to surface the resources that neighborhoods actually need. Contact <a href="mailto:hello@sojorn.net" class="text-egyptianBlue underline">hello@sojorn.net</a> for details.</p>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-bold mt-6 mb-4">8. User Control</h2>
      <p class="mb-4">Users can hide or dismiss any individual sponsored post. We are exploring options for reduced ad frequency or an ad-free experience as a future feature.</p>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-bold mt-6 mb-4">9. Our Commitment</h2>
      <p class="mb-4">Advertising exists to sustain the platform, not to exploit the people who use it. We will never sell your data to advertisers, allow third-party tracking, or let advertisers target individual users. Your in-app activity is used only to improve your experience within Sojorn — it is never exported, sold, or made available outside our systems. If we ever fail to uphold these commitments, our <a href="https://gitlab.com/patrickbritton3/sojorn" class="text-egyptianBlue underline">open-source code</a> is there for anyone to verify.</p>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-bold mt-6 mb-4">10. Contact</h2>
      <p class="mb-4">For advertising inquiries: <a href="mailto:hello@sojorn.net" class="text-egyptianBlue underline">hello@sojorn.net</a>.<br>
        For privacy concerns about advertising: <a href="mailto:privacy@sojorn.net" class="text-egyptianBlue underline">privacy@sojorn.net</a>.</p>
    </div>
  </div>
</Layout>
